{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so the marriage did not last very long.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But she wanted my mother and to join her in the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I didn't want to go, I was making, finally, a life for myself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I loved what I was doing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I had, finally, almost a career, I was making good money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I had a life.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I told my mother, why doesn't she go, see what it's like, with the hope that she wouldn't like it and come back.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then I'll join the later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in 1951, my mother joined my sister.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went into a-- what is best described as an orphanage of boys and girls that were waiting.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were all orphans.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they had lost their fathers and mothers in, in the war, in the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were waiting to-- for their quota to immigrate either to Israel, or to Canada, or to the United States.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were about 50, 50 of us in that orphanage.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's when-- being underage and I was a little bit under 16, my mother made the papers for me to join her in the United States, and I had to come.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I, I did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, I was one of the sole support of that orphanage because I was doing quite well and all the money that I was making was going into the orphanage and-- for use for the other unfortunate other children.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, January 5th, 1952 was the day that they dragged me-- [LAUGHS] --to the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I probably had the worst six months of my life over here because it was like a new beginning again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't speak English, and that was very, very dramatic for me.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
